Abia State’s foremost philanthropist and People’s Democratic Party (PDP) Governorship Aspirant, Chief Ncheta Elvis Omerekpe has reinstated his commitment to run for Abia Governorship Election in 2023 and why he should be trusted for the number one job. Chief Omerekpe who had earlier declared his intention to run for the number one seat in Abia state during a stakeholder’s meeting of Isiala Ngwa North PDP held in his country home, Umuakwu Nsulu, Isiala Ngwa North, LGA of the state. In a statement endorsed by his Director-General, Media Campaign Organisation, Prince Clinton Uba said, the Ngwa born business mogul and PDP aspirant, therefore calls on Abia men, women, most especially the youths to be part of this movement for a better Abia and to join his DIVINE PROJECT VOLUNTEER TEAM. He urged well-meaning Abians to visit his offices at Aba and Umuahia while pledging to deepen the gains of our much-needed dividends of democracy to our dear, state, Abia. He reminded Abians that the Abia of our dream can be achieved if we all work in one accord as Abians, not based on sectional sentiments as hunger and poverty do not recognize where you come from. Chief Ncheta Omerekpe has the capacity, competence and experience to complement the achievements of Gov. Okezie Ikpeazu and indeed, our past leaders. As a man of projects, who has attracted several projects to Abia worth billions, he is no stranger to the development and will enhance infrastructures across all the 17 Local Governments in Abia state if given the Governor of the state. He promised to tackle youth resistivity, unemployment, create an enabling environment for small and medium scale enterprises also create job opportunities, leveraging Agriculture as our destination for growth.